Below is a structured extraction of the **Pradhan Mantri Awas Yojana – Urban 2.0 (PMAY-U 2.0) – Interest Subsidy Scheme (Home Loan)** available through the JanSamarth portal.

---

# Pradhan Mantri Awas Yojana – Urban 2.0 (Interest Subsidy Scheme)

## Overview

| Field                | Value                                                                                |
| -------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ |
| Scheme Name          | Pradhan Mantri Awas Yojana – Urban 2.0 (Interest Subsidy Scheme)                     |
| Ministry             | Ministry of Housing and Urban Affairs (MoHUA)                                        |
| Government Level     | Central Government                                                                   |
| Implementing Portal  | JanSamarth                                                                           |
| Scheme Type          | Home Loan Interest Subsidy                                                           |
| Financial Instrument | Interest Subsidy on Home Loan                                                        |
| Target Beneficiaries | Economically Weaker Section (EWS), Low Income Group (LIG), Middle Income Group (MIG) |
| Objective            | Improve affordable home ownership in urban India through subsidized home loans       |
| Scheme Period        | 1 September 2024 – 31 August 2029 (5 years) ([HDFC Home Loans][1])                   |

---

# Objective

PMAY-U 2.0 aims to help **1 crore urban poor and middle-class families** purchase or construct their first permanent house by reducing the effective cost of a home loan through an interest subsidy. The scheme is part of the Government's "Housing for All" mission. ([HDFC Home Loans][1])

---

# Primary Benefits

## 1. Interest Subsidy

Eligible borrowers receive:

* **4% interest subsidy**
* Applicable on the **first ₹8 lakh** of the home loan
* Maximum loan tenure considered: **12 years**

---

## 2. Maximum Subsidy

* Maximum total subsidy:
  **₹1.80 lakh**

The subsidy is credited directly against the outstanding loan principal in instalments, reducing the effective EMI burden. ([PMAY-HFA][2])

---

## 3. Reduced EMI

Since the subsidy reduces the principal outstanding, borrowers pay lower EMIs over the loan tenure.

---

## 4. Applicable for

The subsidy can be availed for:

* Purchase of a new house
* Construction of a house
* Repurchase (where permitted under scheme guidelines)

([PMAY-HFA][3])

---

# Eligible Beneficiaries

The scheme covers urban households belonging to:

| Category |     Annual Household Income |
| -------- | --------------------------: |
| EWS      |               Up to ₹3 lakh |
| LIG      | Above ₹3 lakh up to ₹6 lakh |
| MIG      | Above ₹6 lakh up to ₹9 lakh |

([PMAY-HFA][3])

---

# Eligibility Criteria

Applicants must satisfy all of the following.

## Income

Annual household income should not exceed **₹9 lakh**.

---

## House Ownership

The applicant or any family member **must not own a pucca house anywhere in India**.

---

## Previous Housing Benefits

The family must **not have previously availed benefits** under any Central Government housing scheme.

---

## Urban Location

The house must be located in an eligible urban area covered under PMAY-U 2.0.

---

## Loan Limits

| Parameter      |  Maximum |
| -------------- | -------: |
| Home Loan      | ₹25 lakh |
| Property Value | ₹35 lakh |

---

## Carpet Area

Maximum carpet area:

**120 sq. metres**

([PMAY-HFA][2])

---

# Women Ownership Requirement

The scheme encourages women-led home ownership. In many cases, the house should be owned by a woman or jointly with a woman, subject to applicable exemptions under the operational guidelines. ([Vastu Housing Finance][4])

